subject: soundcloud privacy: information collected automatically
text:
http://soundcloud.com/pages/privacy#collection
under "Information we collect automatically" there is a non-exhaustive
list of information collected automatically (IP, web visits; browsing
behaviour, searches, device types, etc.)
and the use of cookies is explained in
http://soundcloud.com/pages/privacy#cookies
        Cookies can be “persistent” or “session” cookies. 

And there is a list of third-party cookies (Google, Quantcast,
ATInternet) describing what they do exactly. 

This is better than most 3rd party cookies where it can be any 3rd party
the company sees fit (whereas in a case of soundcloud adding a new 3rd
party, this would result in changes to the policy, hence you have time
to review the change).

Soundcloud also gives plenty of opt-out and information:
http://soundcloud.com/pages/privacy#choices
The section about cookies is particularly relevant to help people
opt-out of 3rd party cookies.
